options.guidance:
Purpose:
This transform matches PTO event information between two data structures, combining them based on meeting names and standardizing field names for easier access.

Input Data Structure:

The first array contains objects with:

Fields ending with "_info" (like "pto_event_tines_guardant_health_info") containing meeting details
"vitally_note_url" fields with relevant URLs
"current_value" fields with meeting names (format: "PTO Event: [meeting name]")
The second array contains meeting objects with:

"text" fields containing the same meeting names (format: "PTO Event: [meeting name]")
Transform Process:

For each meeting object in the second array:
Find the matching info object in the first array where "current_value" equals the meeting's "text"
Find any key in the info object that ends with "_info" and extract its value
Extract the "vitally_note_url" value
Add these as standardized fields to the meeting object
Implementation Code:

from typing import List, Dict

def main(input: List[List[Dict]]):
    meetings = input[1]
    info_objects = input[0]

    for meeting in meetings:
        meeting_name = meeting.get("text")
        for info_object in info_objects:
            if info_object.get("current_value") == meeting_name:
                # Find the key that ends with "_info"
                info_key = None
                for key in info_object:
                    if key.endswith("_info"):
                        info_key = key
                        break
                
                # Get the value from the found key
                if info_key:
                    meeting["info_details"] = info_object.get(info_key)
                meeting["vitally_note_url"] = info_object.get("vitally_note_url")
                break

    return meetings
Expected Output:
Each meeting object will be enhanced with:

An "info_details" field containing the meeting information (extracted from any field ending with "_info")
A "vitally_note_url" field with the relevant URL
All original meeting data preserved
Key Implementation Notes:

The code dynamically finds the correct info field by looking for any key ending with "_info"
This approach handles varying field names without needing to construct the exact key format
The matching is done by comparing the full meeting name strings
If no matching info is found, the fields will remain null
Benefits:

Consolidates related information from different sources
Standardizes dynamic field names for consistent access
Handles varying key formats robustly
Creates a unified view of PTO events with all relevant details

options.guidance:
Find the first two Slack-formatted date blocks in the input. They look like this:

<!date^UNIX_TIMESTAMP^{...}|YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS AM/PM UTC>

Ignore whatâ€™s between the `^` and `|` â€” just extract the UNIX timestamp and the full datetime shown after the `|`.

Return them in this format:

<!date^UNIX_TIMESTAMP_1^YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS AM/PM UTC|YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS AM/PM UTC> - <!date^UNIX_TIMESTAMP_2^YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS AM/PM UTC|YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS AM/PM UTC>

Only return this result, and nothing else.

Example:

Input:
"<!date^1748370600^{date_short_pretty} {time}|2025-05-27 06:30:00 PM UTC> - <!date^1748372400^{time}|2025-05-27 07:00:00 PM UTC>"

Output:
<!date^1748370600^2025-05-27 06:30:00 PM UTC|2025-05-27 06:30:00 PM UTC> - <!date^1748372400^2025-05-27 07:00:00 PM UTC|2025-05-27 07:00:00 PM UTC>

diagram_notes.content:
# Take My Meeting - PTO Coverage Workflow

## Overview
This workflow allows team members to request coverage for meetings while they're on PTO. It automatically:
- Pulls calendar events during selected PTO dates
- Identifies available team members in the same timezone
- Posts a Slack message with claim buttons for each meeting
- Updates messages in real time when meetings are claimed
- Records who took what, when, and from whom

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Required Credentials
- **Slack Bot Token**: Create a Slack app with the following scopes:
  - `channels:read`, `groups:read`, `im:read`, `mpim:read`
  - `users.profile:read`
  - `users:read.email`
  - `chat:write`
- **Google Calendar API**: Create credentials with `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/calendar.readonly` scope

### 2. Record Types
Create two record types in Tines:

#### Team Members Record Type
Fields:
- `real_name` (Text)
- `email` (Text)
- `user_id` (Text)
- `dm_id` (Text)
- `Location Area` (Text)

#### PTO Meeting Record Type
Fields:
- `meeting_id` (Text)
- `record_type` (Text)
- `action_id` (Text)
- `slack_channel_id` (Text)
- `slack_message_ts` (Text)
- `submitter_email` (Text)
- `status` (Text)
- `meeting_details_title` (Text)
- `meeting_details_date` (Timestamp)
- `meeting_details_calendar_event_URL` (Text)
- `posted_at` (Text)
- `claimed_by` (Text)
- `claimed_at_ts` (Text)
- `reminders_count` (Number)
- `last_reminder_at` (Text)
- `submitter_location` (Text)
- `submitter_time_off` (Text)
- `run_id` (Text)
- `meeting_details_vitally` (Text)
- `meeting_details_description` (Text)
- `message_url` (Text)

### 3. Slack Channels
- Create a channel for PTO coverage requests
- Note the channel ID for configuration

### 4. Workflow Configuration
Replace the following placeholders in the workflow:
- All credential references (`CREDENTIAL.your_*`)
- Channel IDs (`YOUR_*_CHANNEL_ID`)
- Webhook path and secret
- Record type IDs
- Record field IDs

### 5. Customization
- Update form text and messaging to match your organization's terminology
- Customize timezone groupings in the workflow if needed
- Update any references to "Team Member" to match your organization's role names

action_inputs.name: Channel / User ID
action_inputs.description: You can use a channel name (like â€˜#generalâ€™) or an ID (like â€˜C1234567890â€™). For non-public channels, specify the ID; this includes private channels, multi-person direct message channels (use the group ID), or DMs to a specific user (use the user ID).

action_inputs.name: Icon emoji
action_inputs.description: Emoji to use as the icon for this message (i.e. :chart_with_upwards_trend:). Overrides Icon URL input.

action_inputs.name: Icon URL
action_inputs.description: URL to an image to use as the icon for this message.

action_inputs.name: Link names?
action_inputs.description: Find and link user groups. No longer supports linking individual users; use syntax shown in [Mentioning Users](https://api.slack.com/reference/surfaces/formatting#mentioning-users) instead.

action_inputs.name: Markdown
action_inputs.description: Select 'no' to disable Slack markup parsing. Enabled by default.

action_inputs.name: Parse
action_inputs.description: Change how messages are treated. See [further details](https://api.slack.com/methods/chat.postMessage#formatting).

action_inputs.name: Send reply to channel?
action_inputs.description: Used in conjunction with input 'Thread timestamp' and indicates whether reply should be made visible to everyone in the channel or conversation. Defaults to false.

action_inputs.name: Thread timestamp
action_inputs.description: Provide another message's ts value to make this message a reply. Avoid using a reply's ts value; use its parent instead.

action_inputs.name: Unfurl media?
action_inputs.description: Select 'no' to disable unfurling of media content.

action_inputs.name: Username
action_inputs.description: Specify your bot's username that will send the message.

action_inputs.name: Message
action_inputs.description: Use [Slack's Block Kit Builder](https://app.slack.com/block-kit-builder) to build your message. Then, click the 'Copy Payload' button on the top right of the block kit builder and paste it into the â€˜Plain codeâ€™ tab here when youâ€™re done.

action_inputs.name: Unfurl links?
action_inputs.description: Select 'yes' to enable unfurling of primarily text-based content.

action_inputs.name: Metadata
action_inputs.description: JSON object with event_type and event_payload fields, presented as a URL-encoded string. Metadata you post to Slack is accessible to any app or user who is a member of that workspace. ex: {"event_type": "task_created", "event_payload": { "id": "11223", "title": "Redesign Homepage"}}

action_inputs.name: Calendar ID
action_inputs.description: Calendar identifier. To retrieve calendar IDs call the calendarList.list method. If you want to access the primary calendar of the currently logged in user, use the "primary" keyword.

action_inputs.name: Sync token
action_inputs.description:
Token obtained from the nextSyncToken field returned on the last page of results from the previous list request. It makes the result of this list request contain only entries that have changed since then. All events deleted since the previous list request will always be in the result set and it is not allowed to set showDeleted to False.
There are several query parameters that cannot be specified together with nextSyncToken to ensure consistency of the client state.

action_inputs.name: Private extended property
action_inputs.description: Extended properties constraint specified as propertyName=value. Matches only private properties. This parameter might be repeated multiple times to return events that match all given constraints.

action_inputs.name: Shared extended property
action_inputs.description: Extended properties constraint specified as propertyName=value. Matches only shared properties. This parameter might be repeated multiple times to return events that match all given constraints.

action_inputs.name: Q
action_inputs.description: Free text search terms to find events that match these terms

action_inputs.name: Updated min
action_inputs.description: Lower bound for an event's last modification time (as a RFC3339 timestamp) to filter by. When specified, entries deleted since this time will always be included regardless of showDeleted. The default is not to filter by last modification time.

action_inputs.name: iCal UID
action_inputs.description: Specifies an event ID in the iCalendar format to be provided in the response. Use this if you want to search for an event by its iCalendar ID.

action_inputs.name: Time zone
action_inputs.description: Time zone used in the response. The default is the time zone of the calendar.

action_inputs.name: Show hidden invitations
action_inputs.description: Whether to include hidden invitations in the result. The default is False.

action_inputs.name: Page token
action_inputs.description: Token specifying which result page to return.

action_inputs.name: Max results
action_inputs.description: Maximum number of events returned on one result page. The number of events in the resulting page may be less than this value, or none at all, even if there are more events matching the query. Incomplete pages can be detected by a non-empty nextPageToken field in the response. By default the value is 250 events. The page size can never be larger than 2500 events.

action_inputs.name: Max attendees
action_inputs.description: The maximum number of attendees to include in the response. If there are more than the specified number of attendees, only the participant is returned.

action_inputs.name: Time max
action_inputs.description: Upper bound (exclusive) for an event's start time to filter by. The default is not to filter by start time. Must be an RFC3339 timestamp with mandatory time zone offset, for example, 2011-06-03T10:00:00-07:00, 2011-06-03T10:00:00Z. Milliseconds may be provided but are ignored. If timeMin is set, timeMax must be greater than timeMin.

action_inputs.name: Time min
action_inputs.description: Lower bound (exclusive) for an event's end time to filter by. The default is not to filter by end time. Must be an RFC3339 timestamp with mandatory time zone offset, for example, 2011-06-03T10:00:00-07:00, 2011-06-03T10:00:00Z. Milliseconds may be provided but are ignored. If timeMax is set, timeMin must be smaller than timeMax.

action_inputs.name: Order by
action_inputs.description: The order of the events returned in the result. The default is an unspecified, stable order.

action_inputs.name: Single events
action_inputs.description: Whether to expand recurring events into instances and only return single one-off events and instances of recurring events, but not the underlying recurring events themselves. The default is False.

action_inputs.name: Show deleted
action_inputs.description: Whether to include deleted events (with status equals "cancelled") in the result. Cancelled instances of recurring events (but not the underlying recurring event) will still be included if showDeleted and singleEvents are both False. If showDeleted and singleEvents are both True, only single instances of deleted events (but not the underlying recurring events) are returned. The default is False.

action_inputs.name: Event types
action_inputs.description: Event types to return. This parameter can be repeated multiple times to return events of different types. The default is ["default", "focusTime", "outOfOffice"].

action_inputs.name: Trigger ID
action_inputs.description: A `trigger_id` received from another interaction

action_inputs.name: View Object
action_inputs.description:
